rComments: His lectures were mediocre and not really that interesting. Assignments were easy as long as you listened to your TAs. He basically gave you the questions of the final exam beforehand as well. Nice guy though, definitely more of an academic than a teacher. Would take again.

His lectures were much more interesting in 256 than 103, not mandatory but good for context and tells you exactly what to look for in the tests that isn't in the test review. Had problems with some marks from my TAs and he turned my final grade from a B- to a B+ (beware that he can take a lifetime to reply to emails but it's worth contacting him)

Barely read the textbook, never went to class, all you need to do is develop a good essay, reach out to your TA for tips. Prof basically gives you the test outline before the midterm and the final so study the topics in the outlines (I wikied most of the topics) and you'll be good. Only issue is Graham is bad at replying to emails.
Read the textbook and you should be fine

I took EAS103 with him and he was great! He is very passionate about what he is teaching. He cares about his students and he is encouraging towards us. It was amazing that he had a revision for the essay assignment which boosts my marks.
He gives passionate lectures. light work, good grade.
EAS256 is considered to be a bird course, but Prof. Sanders is amazing! He is a very knowledgable person, always happy to help after class. A very nice person and great instructor overall!!!
He is the best prof. in U of T. He has a loving heart for all of his students and being helpful for all times. His modest attitude and respecting students makes him respectful! Love him!
THE BEST PROF I'VE EVER SEEN IN U OF T. HE IS THE BEST. I ABSOLUTELY LOVE HIM.

One of the best profs. Lectures are crystal clear with interesting slides. Even people who not interested - will like the topic. Tests are not hard. Very considerate as to breaks and questions. Very friendly with technology. Loved it.

He's not the best professor out there, and can be a little dull at times, but I think he's still pretty good! He's very passionate in his own field of study, Chinese poetry, and China in general. He's a very nice man, and is very generous with the marking scheme. The final exam was extremely easy as he essentially told us exactly what it was on.

The subject was interesting; however, I found the lectures very boring. He uploaded the slides but I they were mostly useless: 90% of them are just pictures. It is hard to understand the main points of his lectures if you don't read the weekly chapter and extra sources.
Lectures were dull and not engaging. Power-points seemed to be used for his own purposes. He seems nice enough but would never recommend this Professor.
Helpful, lectures were interesting and fun! :)
Great Prof, get to know him, and if you think T.A marks unfairly go up to him and he will resolve it and mark it himself (and he marks really kindly), great guy in general, into his studies.
